				\begin{document}$$ J(P, C) = |P \cap C |/|P \cup C| . $$\end{document}As we see, the index gives us the ratio of the size of the intersection of P and C to the size of their union. The index ranges from 0 to 1, where an index of 1 indicates that the sets completely intersect, and thus, have the same elements. As the value approaches to 0 the sets are a more diverse among themselves.

